There were some problems when I tried to use the Query History Visualization Tool.

I enanbled the setting `http_service` in iotdb-engine.properties and started the IoTDB server. I tried to visit the webpage `localhost:8181` but recieved the message `HTTP ERROR 404 Not Found`. The same problem would not be reproduced in release/0.9.2..

Then I tried to open the index.html file directly (by double-clink) and I found following problems.

1. The request of http://localhost:8181/rest/server_information was not polling, and the server information would not be updated after the page was loaded. (It seems that the same problem is in release/0.9.x)

2. When I sent the request 'http://localhost:8181/rest/sql_arguments' in the brower's address bar, I would recieved the right response. But I notied that when the brower sent the request in the background, the brower would recieved `Access to fetch at 'http://localhost:8181/rest/sql_arguments' from origin 'null' has been blocked by CORS policy: Response to preflight request doesn't pass access control check: It does not have HTTP ok status.` The recieved message could be found in the web console.
